@node USAGE "Usage"

    @{b}ElAssign@{ub} has the following command line template:

        @{FG shine}ElAssign.REXX@{FG text} @{b}NAME@{ub} [@{b}DELETE@{ub} | @{b}KILL@{ub}] [@{b}NODEEP@{ub}]


        @{b}NAME@{ub} is the name of the file/directory to remove the assigns from.
        If NAME has spaces in it, it @{b}must@{ub} be enclosed with double quotes.

        @{b}DELETE@{ub} deletes the directory but only if you confirm whilst
        @{b}KILL@{ub} is a silent killer ;) Default is not to delete anything.
        @{b}DELETE@{ub} will override @{b}KILL@{ub} if you "accidentaly" put them both
        into the command line.

        @{b}NODEEP@{ub} instructs the script only to remove assigns from the
        argument you specified (file or directory) and not to go
        deep in the jungles of the directory (you can't go into
        the file, can you?).


  @{b}Usage@{ub}:

    @{i}From Shell:@{ui}

        [RX] FullPath:ToScript/ElAssign.REXX @{b}NAME@{ub} [@{b}DELETE@{ub} | @{b}KILL@{ub}] [@{b}NODEEP@{ub}]

    @{b}DOpus4@{ub}:

      @{i}Configuration/Buttons@{ui}:


@{" AmigaDOS " link } RX FullPath:ToScript/ElAssign.REXX "{f}" [DELETE | KILL] [NODEEP]


        You might want to select @{b}Do all files@{ub}.
        You can also set up a hotkey for the button.

    @{b}DOpus5@{ub}:

        I don't have DOpus5 but it's fairly easy to set this script up
        with it. Please consult your DOpus5 manual to see how to do it.
        Looking at installation instructions for DOpus4 (@{b}{f}@{ub} is file name
        which should be enclosed with double quotes) might help.

        Oh, yes. "El" in @{FG shine}ElAssign@{FG text} doesn't have anything to do with Spain.
        It's short from Eliminate :)

        Finally, if you find any bugs or have some suggestions, please
        contact @{" me " link Author}.
@endnode
