@node FEATURES "Features"



    @{" " link  } It will remove all assigns from a directory and all its
       subdirectories and files unless NODEEP option is specified.

    @{" " link  } It works with everything including DOpus4, DOpus5 and
       any other kind of filemanager programs.

    @{" " link  } You can optionally delete chosen directory with all its
       contents. You can specify DELETE for deleting the directory with
       confirmation and KILL for deleting without confirmation.

    @{" " link  } You can give any kind of path to the directory/file:
       using complete path, relative path or assign.

@endnode
@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

        Have you ever downloaded a file from Aminet and decided to try
    it, so you unpack it to a directory. You start it and find out that
    it needs an assign or two to work. Fine, you assign necessary things
    and try the program. You decide you don't like it and want to delete
    the directory you unpacked it to but you descover that you can't becouse
    it and/or it's subdirectories have assigns. Then you need to deassign
    @{b}all of them@{ub} which can be very boring. Instead of starting a shell
    and typing all the commands in it, you can just start ElAssign and it
    will do all the work for you and (optionally) delete the directory for
    you with or without asking. The idea came from Charles Petterson who
    wrote DeAsssign.dopus5 but I wrote ElAssign from scratch and added
    few @{" features " link Features}.
@endnode
